<section xml:id="double-angle_and_half-angle_formulas">
  <title>Double-Angle and Half-Angle Formulas</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>
      Suppose we want to accurately position the Hawaiian Star Compass on the Unit Circle. In Figure*******
      <!-- <xref ref="star-compass-32-compass-rose"/>, -->
       the house for Manu is located at halfway between Hikina and ʻĀkau, resulting in an angle of <m>45^{\circ}</m>. By applying right triangle trigonometry, we can determine the exact coordinates of Manu as <m>\left(\cos(45^{\circ}), \sin(45^{\circ})\right) = \left(\frac{\sqrt{2}}{2}, \frac{\sqrt{2}}{2}\right)</m>. However, as we move to the house of ʻĀina, located halfway between Manu and Hikina, we encounter a problem. The angle for ʻĀina is <m>22.5^{\circ}</m>, which is not explicitly listed listed in Table 1.5.18 ***************
      <!-- <xref ref="tab_trig-table"/>. -->
      Therefore, we must resort to a calculator for numerical approximations.
     </p>
     <image xml:id="fig-quad1-Koolau-manu-aina-angles" width="80%">
      <latex-image>
        \begin{tikzpicture}[scale=6.75]
        % draw the coordinates
        \draw[dashed] (0cm,0cm) -- (0.73cm,0cm);
        \draw[-stealth,dashed] (0.97cm,0cm) -- (1.05cm,0cm);
        \draw[dashed] (0cm,0cm) -- (0cm,0.76cm);
        \draw[-stealth,dashed] (0cm,0.98cm) -- (0cm,1.05cm);
        % draw the unit circle
        \draw[thick] (0:1cm) arc (0:90:1cm);
        \draw[left] (0:0.98) node[rotate=0] {\large HIKINA};
        \draw[left] (90:0.98) node[rotate=90] {\large `\={A}KAU};
        
        \draw (0:1.05) node[right] {$\left(\cos0^{\circ},\sin0^{\circ}\right)=(1,0)$};
        \draw (22.5:1.05) node[right] {$\left(\cos22.5^{\circ},\sin22.5^{\circ}\right)=(?,?)$};
        \draw (45:1.05) node[right] {$\left(\cos45^{\circ},\sin45^{\circ}\right)=\left(\frac{\sqrt{2}}{2},\frac{\sqrt{2}}{2}\right)$};
        \draw (90:1.05) node[right] {$\left(\cos90^{\circ},\sin90^{\circ}\right)=(0,1)$};
        \foreach \x/\xtext in {
        22.5/{`\={A}ina, $22.5^{\circ}$},
